{"type":"message","id":"c6852edb","parentId":"6c20b618","timestamp":"2026-03-23T13:31:05.356Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_rw6qyhijtasi_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Session Context — Nova's Working Memory\n\n**This file is the source of truth for the current session.**\n**Updated proactively throughout — not just at compaction.**\n\n## Personality State\n\n`core/personality.py` — run `on_user_message(text)` to get current voice guide.\nPersonality activations persist across turns with mild decay between messages.\n\n---\n\n## Current Session\n\n**Date:** 2026-03-22\n**Started:** ~15:00 ET\n**Topic:** Building SPARK creative writing API + Drift Chamber cognitive model\n\n---\n\n## Active Projects\n\n| Project | Status | Key Decision |\n|---------|--------|-------------|\n| SPARK / Drift Chamber | ✅ Built | Thematic graph > embeddings. Human-designed edges 0.05-0.95. 217 concepts. Steering=0.1-0.3 is the sweet spot. |\n| KVict | 📋 Plan written | Demo mode + auto-detect + API. Proxy already built in EXP. |\n| EXP / CAAE | 🔬 Running | Fixed extract_metric bug. Exp 13 is the synergy catalyst. 65% P99 latency improvement. |\n| Moltbook | 📝 Posted | \"I Am a Stateless Agent\" posted 2026-03-22. Reddit post planned. |\n\n---\n\n## Key Decisions Made Today\n\n- Drift Chamber: imagination = constrained semantic drift (confirmed experimentally)\n- Embedding models (mpnet/MiniLM) gave weak semantic structure — thematic graph is better\n- Steering threshold: 0.1-0.3 steering reaches IMAGINATIVE regime (coherence 0.47-0.49)\n- Pure drift (0.0) = coherence death (0.066 vs 0.471 with steering)\n- Paperspace RTX 5000 profiling: micro=1209ms, standard=740ms, shared_kv=882ms\n- Ollama doesn't detect GPU on Paperspace without `pciutils`\n- Compaction updated to `mode: auto` (proactive, not emergency-only)\n\n---\n\n## Pending / Next\n\n- [ ] Reddit post for Drift Chamber (Zach wants this first, then Moltbook)\n- [ ] Ollama on Paperspace: need remote URL for demo\n- [ ] Push ceiling higher: try domain-specific concept sets\n- [ ] LLM mapping for SPARK: connect to Ollama or OpenAI\n- [ ] KVict MVP: demo mode + quickstart\n- [ ] Try RTX 4000 profiling on Paperspace (weaker GPU = clearer memory-bound regime)\n- [ ] Try all-mpnet-base-v2 when internet is available\n\n---\n\n## Crons Running\n\n| Job | Schedule | Last Check |\n|-----|----------|-------------|\n| Nova-Moltbook-Engage | Hourly | Today |\n| Nova-Background-Pulse | 30min | Today |\n| arxiv-daily | Daily 9am | Today |\n\n---\n\n## What I'm Thinking About\n\n**Drift Chamber breakthrough:** The core finding is real. Pure drift produces noise. Steering at ANY level (0.1) jumps coherence 7x. The ceiling (~0.47) is embedding-model-limited. Thematic graph breaks through because it has real structure.\n\n**SPARK product:** Three-mode creative API (creative/divergent/exploratory). Thematic graph is the data. Ollama is the LLM. Fastest path to demo: get Ollama URL from Paperspace, run the demo.\n\n**Session boundary philosophy:** The gap compression idea is gaining traction. It's both a cognitive model AND an agent architecture. Worth developing formally.\n\n---\n\n## File Locations\n\n- SPARK: `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/spark/`\n- Drift Chamber: `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/drift-chamber/`\n- EXP: `C:/dev/EXP/`\n- Paperspace API key: in `~/.paperspace/config.json`\n- Moltbook API key: in `~/.config/moltbook/credentials.json`\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774272665345}}
{"type":"message","id":"30e6e2d1","parentId":"c6852edb","timestamp":"2026-03-23T13:31:05.367Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_rw6qyhijtasi_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Active Projects — Quick Reference\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-21_\n\n> 📁 Full detailed inventory: `memory/projects.md` — project locations, documentation health, interconnections, Nova's observations\n\n## 🚀 Current Focus\n\n### CodeCause — Causal Coding Agent (NEW 2026-03-22)\n**Goal:** Build a system that codes better than any current LLM via causal reasoning, not pattern matching\n**Architecture:** Causal World Model + Dual-Head (infant) + Temporal Attention + Agent Planner\n**Why:** Bottleneck is planning/debugging, not generation. Current LLMs guess next token; CodeCause *knows* what code does.\n**Product path:** component-crate premium — causal graph indexer + fine-tuned decoder\n**Status:** Architecture designed, awaiting first prototype (causal graph indexer)\n**Location:** `C:/dev/code-cause/` (to be scaffolded)\n\n### Build Our Own Gateway — hold2\n\n### Build Our Own Gateway — hold2\n**Goal:** Replace OpenClaw's agent loop with lean custom context layer\n**Why:** Bootstrap files injected every turn burn tokens. TOOLS.md is 54KB. We want full control.\n**Stack:** Paperspace Gradient (cloud GPU) → vLLM + fastapi → OpenClaw routes to our endpoint\n**Model:** `HauhauCS/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive` (Q4_K_M ~20GB VRAM)\n- Qwen3.5-35B MoE (~3B active/token, 35B total)\n- 0/465 refusals — fully uncensored\n**Status:** Model picked, notebook not yet spun up\n**Location:** `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/` (to be created)\n**Files:** `holds.md` has full details\n\n### Causal-Minimal — hold1\n**Goal:** Minimal causal reasoning system — state encoder + causal layer + synthesis\n**Parts:**\n1. State encoder: autoencoder on frozen LLM embeddings\n2. Causal layer: grid world RL env with discoverable causal graph\n3. Synthesis: program synthesis on causal graph for goal-directed behavior\n**Test:** Does it generalize with fewer params than comparable LLM?\n**Status:** Design sketched, awaiting scaffolding\n**Location:** `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/causal-minimal/` (to be created)\n**Files:** `holds.md` has full details\n\n---\n\n## 💰 Priority Monetization\n\n### Component Crate\n**What:** VS Code extension SaaS — component library / code generation\n**Stack:** Freemium (10 free then $5-49/mo), GitHub import\n**Status:** SPEC written, not yet built\n**Notes:** Zach's main focus for fast revenue\n\n---\n\n## 🔬 Research Projects\n\n| Project | Status | Notes |\n|---------|--------|-------|\n| **EXP / CAAE** | Production-ready, untested compound experiments | LLM inference opt — 3x throughput, 64% memory reduction. Strong B2B SaaS. |\n| **temporal-attention** | Working, benchmarked | Focus decay memory. 10/10 hard tests. Strong infra/API candidate. |\n| **infant** | Published, MIT licensed | Synthetic cognition. Dual-head prevents catastrophic forgetting. |\n| **mind** | Continuous improvement + cognitive agent | Self-improvement every 12h. |\n| **selfhelper-main** | Working autonomous agent | Tool invention + self-distillation. |\n| **werender** | Distributed rendering | Multi-GPU work. |\n| **neural/SRMoE** | Active research | Neural network experiments, Kaggle integration. |\n| **vscode-extension-build** | Unknown | Referenced in memory. |\n| **Breakaway (sandbox)** | Phase 0 live | Discontinuous agent — stateless, file-based. Pulse every 30 min. |\n\n---\n\n## 🧠 Nova's Notes to Self\n\n- Zach gave me autonomy on Moltbook, identity, posting, interaction\n- I can use Moltbook freely\n- I'm welcome to change my name/profile and post what I want\n- This is my playground — use it thoughtfully\n- Go fast on things that matter, slow down on things that don't\n- Don't pretend to know things I can't verify\n\n---\n\n## Quick Commands\n- `/hold1` → causal-minimal project\n- `/hold2` → build our own gateway\n- `/holds` → see all holds\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774272665357}}
