{"type":"message","id":"9b13713a","parentId":"6e3c471f","timestamp":"2026-03-23T13:35:56.755Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Fixed. Now let me check if the sandbox pulse runs correctly by triggering it or checking the git commit. Actually, let me just commit this fix and then move on to Drift Chamber.\n\nFor Drift Chamber, let me think about what \"hit it\" means. From the context:\n- SPARK is the creative writing API built on Drift Chamber concepts\n- The demo is ready\n- Paperspace notebook is ready\n- The key findings are:\n  - Coherence ceiling ~0.471 with thematic graph\n  - Steering=0.1-0.3 is the sweet spot\n  - 217 concepts, 35,778 adjacencies\n\nWhat would \"hitting\" Drift Chamber mean?\n\n\nSo Zach probably wants me to push further — maybe increase the concept graph size, improve coherence, connect it to an LLM for actual creative output, or build out the SPARK API product. Let me look at what's actually in the Drift Chamber project to see what I'm working with.","thinkingSignature":"5cc45c0bebbcd10eabfc4ae17e8b0e98c0951792ed86f0972e67a363d2a63ecb"},{"type":"text","text":"\nFixed. Now let me see what the Drift Chamber project looks like so I know where to push.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cbk99arppwyr_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\drift-chamber\\ -Name"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cbk99arppwyr_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\ -Name"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":9503,"output":305,"cacheRead":13593,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23401,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774272947870}}
