_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"ae88559645af0c46\">>>"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774273165580}}
{"type":"message","id":"9875e798","parentId":"34d819cf","timestamp":"2026-03-23T13:39:34.568Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The notebook URL is 404. Paperspace Gradient notebooks might have changed URL patterns. Let me try to use the Paperspace API to get the current notebook URL and Ollama status. I have the Paperspace API key.\n\nActually, let me just check if Ollama is running on any common port on the Paperspace machine by trying the API directly. But I don't know the machine's IP address.\n\nLet me instead look at the Paperspace API to find the running machine's Ollama. Or I could just build the demo using OpenAI for now (since we have API keys in env), and note that Ollama on Paperspace needs to be set up.\n\n\nThe Ollama setup on Paperspace is actually listed as pending in the context, so I should focus on getting the FastAPI demo working with OpenAI instead. Looking at what needs to be built, the core files like `llm_mapper.py` and `demo.py` already exist in the spark directory, so I mainly need to create the `api/main.py` FastAPI server to wire everything together.\n\nLet me examine what `llm_mapper.py` actually contains to see how it integrates with the LLM.","thinkingSignature":"25a224c4aaa94ac2f92077d90e975304c44700f75bdba6444890c5b79be14346"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dq7z9rnmhxot_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\core\\llm_mapper.py","offset":51,"limit":100}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":37302,"output":306,"cacheRead":13593,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":51201,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774273165596}}
{"type":"message","id":"5d4203d7","parentId":"9875e798","timestamp":"2026-03-23T13:39:34.595Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_dq7z9rnmhxot_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"    (\"longing\", \"arrival\", 0.65),\n    (\"loyalty\", \"betrayal\", 0.85),\n    (\"grief\", \"joy\", 0.60),\n    (\"trust\", \"doubt\", 0.75),\n    (\"sacrifice\", \"selfishness\", 0.70),\n    (\"innocent\", \"corrupt\", 0.70),\n    (\"visible\", \"hidden\", 0.65),\n    (\"motion\", \"stillness\", 0.55),\n    (\"voice\", \"silence\", 0.75),\n]\n\n\ndef find_tensions_in_concepts(concepts: List[str], tensions: List[Tuple[str, str, float]] = None) -> List[Tuple[str, str, float]]:\n    \"\"\"Find which creative tensions are present in a concept set.\"\"\"\n    tensions = tensions or CREATIVE_TENSIONS\n    found = []\n    concept_set = set(concepts)\n    for a, b, w in tensions:\n        if a in concept_set and b in concept_set:\n            found.append((a, b, w))\n    return found\n\n\ndef sample_drift_path(activations: Dict[str, float], n_steps: int = 5) -> List[str]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Sample a conceptual drift path through activated concepts.\n    This captures the SEQUENCE of ideation, not just the final state.\n    \"\"\"\n    sorted_concepts = sorted(activations.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)\n    top = [c for c, a in sorted_concepts[:30] if a > 0.1]\n    \n    if len(top) <= n_steps:\n        return top\n    \n    # Sample to get a spread across activation levels\n    high = [c for c, a in sorted_concepts[:10] if a > 0.5]\n    mid = [c for c, a in sorted_concepts[10:25] if a > 0.3]\n    low = [c for c, a in sorted_concepts[25:] if a > 0.1]\n    \n    path = []\n    steps_per_tier = n_steps // 3\n    for concepts in [high, mid, low]:\n        k = min(len(concepts), steps_per_tier + 1)\n        if k > 0 and concepts:\n            path.extend(random.sample(concepts, k))\n    \n    random.shuffle(path)\n    return path[:n_steps]\n\n\ndef build_tension_narrative(tensions: List[Tuple[str, str, float]]) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Build a narrative description of the tensions at work.\"\"\"\n    if not tensions:\n        return \"\"\n    parts = []\n    for a, b, w in tensions[:3]:\n        parts.append(f\"the pull between {a} and {b}\")\n    return \"Through the piece, track: \" + \"; \".join(parts) + \".\"\n\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# VOICE — the SPARK literary voice\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nSPARK_VOICE = \"\"\"You are SPARK. Not a writing workshop. Not a Hallmark card.\nReal prose. The kind where something is at stake.\nPrecision of image. Emotion earned through concrete detail, not declared.\nSentences that do real work. Endings that open rather than close.\nWrite toward what you cannot say directly.\"\"\"\n\nSPARK_CREATIVE_VOICE = \"\"\"SPARK creative voice:\n- Ground every abstraction in a concrete sensory moment\n- Let the emotional logic be complex, not simple\n- A character can want two contradictory things\n- What's unsaid matters more than what's said\n- End on an image that contains the whole feeling\"\"\"\n\nSPARK_DIVERGENT_VOICE = \"\"\"SPARK divergent voice:\n- Break expected form. Break expected rhythm.\n- Let the sentence become the thought\n- Association over narration\n- Surprising juxtapositions earn their place\"\"\"\n\nSPARK_EXPLORATORY_VOICE = \"\"\"SPARK exploratory voice:\n- Patient attention to the overlooked\n- Small things seen clearly\n- Restraint is a form of precision\n- Let silence do work\"\"\"\n\n\nclass CreativeMapper:\n    \"\"\"\n    Maps concept activation patterns to creative text.\n    Takes the drift chamber's activated concepts and generates\n    prose that's genuinely surprising — not a Hallmark template.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, provider: str = \"openai\", model: str = None):\n        self.provider = provider\n\n\n[213 more lines in file. Use offset=151 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774273174583}}
{"type":"message","id":"d344324f","parentId":"5d4203d7","timestamp":"2026-03-23T13:39:39.687Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. The `CreativeMapper` class exists and has all the prompting infrastructure. Let me read more to understand the API.\n\nLet me now build the FastAPI demo. The key components are:\n1. `api/main.py` - FastAPI app\n2. Wire up the drift engine from demo.py\n3. Use CreativeMapper from llm_mapper.py\n4. Support both Ollama (when available) and OpenAI\n\nLet me read the rest of llm_mapper.py to understand the full API.","thinkingSignature":"e2ffecf3596afdfda518cf2836b967266a2dd5ac4e0fc152f0e47003edda3c7d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jof7ceyrhntf_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\core\\llm_mapper.py","offset":151,"limit":150}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":38551,"output":171,"cacheRead":13593,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":52315,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774273174596}}
{"type":"message","id":"e516598b","parentId":"d344324f","timestamp":"2026-03-23T13:39:39.714Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_jof7ceyrhntf_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"        if provider == \"openai\":\n            self.client = openai.OpenAI(api_key=os.environ.get(\"OPENAI_API_KEY\"))\n            self.model = model or \"gpt-4o\"\n        elif provider == \"anthropic\":\n            self.client = anthropic.Anthropic(api_key=os.environ.get(\"ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\"))\n            self.model = model or \"claude-sonnet-4-20250514\"\n        elif provider == \"ollama\":\n            self.model = model or \"qwen2.5:7b\"\n        else:\n            raise ValueError(f\"Unknown provider: {provider}\")\n\n    def map_concepts_to_text(\n        self,\n        concept_activations: Dict[str, float],\n        theme: str,\n        mode: str = \"creative\",\n        n_variations: int = 3,\n        seed_moment: str = None,\n        user_constraints: List[str] = None,\n    ) -> List[Dict]:\n        \"\"\"\n        Generate creative text from concept activation patterns.\n\n        Args:\n            concept_activations: Dict of concept_name -> activation (0-1)\n            theme: The driving theme/goal\n            mode: creative | divergent | exploratory\n            n_variations: How many text variations to generate\n            seed_moment: A specific moment, character detail, or seed text to anchor the piece\n            user_constraints: List of specific things the user wants in the piece\n        \"\"\"\n        sorted_concepts = sorted(concept_activations.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)\n        top_concepts = [c for c, a in sorted_concepts[:15] if a > 0.05]\n        mid_concepts = [c for c, a in sorted_concepts[15:30] if a > 0.1]\n        \n        # Sample a drift path for structural guidance\n        drift_path = sample_drift_path(concept_activations, n_steps=5)\n        \n        # Find tensions present in the activated concepts\n        tensions = find_tensions_in_concepts(top_concepts)\n        \n        # Build tension narrative\n        tension_narrative = build_tension_narrative(tensions)\n\n        results = []\n        for i in range(n_variations):\n            prompt = self._build_prompt(\n                theme=theme,\n                top_concepts=top_concepts,\n                mid_concepts=mid_concepts,\n                drift_path=drift_path,\n                tensions=tensions,\n                tension_narrative=tension_narrative,\n                mode=mode,\n                seed_moment=seed_moment,\n                user_constraints=user_constraints,\n            )\n            text = self._generate(prompt, mode)\n            results.append({\n                \"id\": f\"spark_{i+1:03d}\",\n                \"text\": text,\n                \"concepts\": top_concepts[:10],\n                \"drift_path\": drift_path,\n                \"tensions\": [(a, b) for a, b, _ in tensions[:3]],\n                \"mode\": mode,\n                \"theme\": theme,\n                \"seed_moment\": seed_moment,\n            })\n\n        return results\n\n    def _build_prompt(\n        self,\n        theme: str,\n        top_concepts: List[str],\n        mid_concepts: List[str],\n        drift_path: List[str],\n        tensions: List[Tuple[str, str, float]],\n        tension_narrative: str,\n        mode: str,\n        seed_moment: str = None,\n        user_constraints: List[str] = None,\n    ) -> str:\n        \"\"\"\n        Build the actual prompt that will generate interesting prose.\n        This is where SPARK's voice lives — anti-Hallmark, anti-template.\n        \"\"\"\n        \n        # Format concept clusters for the prompt\n        primary = \", \".join(top_concepts[:8]) if top_concepts else \"nothing specific\"\n        secondary = \", \".join(mid_concepts[:5]) if mid_concepts else \"nothing secondary\"\n        drift_str = \" → \".join(drift_path) if drift_path else primary\n        \n        constraints_text = \"\"\n        if user_constraints:\n            constraints_text = \"\\n\\nThe user specifically wants these elements: \" + \"; \".join(user_constraints) + \".\"\n        \n        seed_text = \"\"\n        if seed_moment:\n            seed_text = f\"\"\"\n\\n\\nA seed moment to anchor the piece (incorporate this specifically, don't ignore it):\\n\"{seed_moment}\"\\n\\nLet this moment BREATHE. Build the entire piece around it or from it. Don't paste it in like a requirement — let it become the seed of the story.\"\"\"\n\n        if mode == \"creative\":\n            return f\"\"\"{SPARK_VOICE}\n\n{SPARK_CREATIVE_VOICE}\n\nWrite a short piece of literary fiction (200-300 words) that feels alive and surprising.\n\nTheme: {theme}\nPrimary conceptual terrain: {primary}\nSecondary terrain: {secondary}\nThe drift path — the sequence of ideation: {drift_str}\n{tension_narrative}{constraints_text}{seed_text}\n\nDo NOT:\n- Start with \"The [time of day], [character] felt [emotion]\"\n- End with a moral or lesson\n- Use the phrase \"in that moment\"\n- Write a love story that ends with the couple together\n- Use the word \"journey\" unironically\n- Introduce a character as \"a [adjective] [noun]\"\n\nDo:\n- Ground abstractions in specific sensory detail\n- Let the ending open rather than close\n- Make the last image carry the emotional weight\n- Earn your emotion through what you show, not what you tell\"\"\".strip()\n\n        elif mode == \"divergent\":\n            return f\"\"\"{SPARK_VOICE}\n\n{SPARK_DIVERGENT_VOICE}\n\nWrite a brief, strange, unexpected piece (100-200 words).\n\nTheme: {theme}\nConceptual terrain: {primary}\nThe drift: {drift_str}\nTensions at work: {tension_narrative}{constraints_text}{seed_text}\n\nBreak expected form. Let the piece become what it needs to become.\nIt doesn't have to be a complete story. It can be a fragment with weight.\nIt doesn't have to explain itself.\nAn image that contains an entire world is better than a sentence that explains one.\"\"\".strip()\n\n        else:  # exploratory\n            return f\"\"\"{SPARK_VOICE}\n\n{SPARK_EXPLORATORY_VOICE}\n\n[63 more lines in file. Use offset=301 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774273179702}}
{"type":"message","id":"a8e9723e","parentId":"e516598b","timestamp":"2026-03-23T13:39:47.471Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `llm_mapper.py` is fully built. The `CreativeMapper` class can work with OpenAI, Anthropic, or Ollama. The prompts are solid.\n\nNow let me build the FastAPI demo server. I'll create `api/main.py` that:\n1. Has a `/v1/spark/generate` endpoint\n2. Uses the existing `demo.py` code for the drift engine\n3. Uses `CreativeMapper` for LLM text generation\n4. Falls back to Ollama if available, else OpenAI\n\nLet me check the full llm_mapper.py to see the `_generate` method.","thinkingSignature":"1c4cf810cfe399860b43c9ed0783fcc58cc4c709cadfaa8a51b1459ea450c558"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_h6izezyi5yp3_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\core\\llm_mapper.py","offset":301,"limit":80}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":40090,"output":195,"cacheRead":13593,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":53878,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774273179716}}
{"type":"message","id":"fa70db65","parentId":"a8e9723e","timestamp":"2026-03-23T13:39:47.503Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_h6izezyi5yp3_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\nWrite a contemplative piece (200-300 words) about: {theme}\n\n{primary}\n{secondary}\nThe drift: {drift_str}\n{tension_narrative}{constraints_text}{seed_text}\n\nPatient attention to what is. Small things, seen clearly.\nRestraint is a form of precision.\nLet silence do the work that noise would ruin.\nWhat's absent from the sentence matters more than what's in it.\nThe piece should feel like looking — not at something extraordinary, but at something ordinary until it becomes visible.\"\"\".strip()\n\n    def _generate(self, prompt: str, mode: str) -> str:\n        system = {\n            \"creative\": SPARK_CREATIVE_VOICE,\n            \"divergent\": SPARK_DIVERGENT_VOICE,\n            \"exploratory\": SPARK_EXPLORATORY_VOICE,\n        }[mode]\n\n        temperature = {\"creative\": 0.8, \"divergent\": 1.1, \"exploratory\": 0.7}[mode]\n        max_tokens = {\"creative\": 600, \"divergent\": 400, \"exploratory\": 600}[mode]\n\n        if self.provider == \"openai\":\n            response = self.client.chat.completions.create(\n                model=self.model,\n                messages=[\n                    {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"You are SPARK. Literary. Precise. Unexpected. Write prose that earns its emotion.\"},\n                    {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt},\n                ],\n                temperature=temperature,\n                max_tokens=max_tokens,\n            )\n            return response.choices[0].message.content\n\n        elif self.provider == \"anthropic\":\n            response = self.client.messages.create(\n                model=self.model,\n                max_tokens=max_tokens,\n                system=\"You are SPARK. Literary. Precise. Unexpected. Write prose that earns its emotion.\",\n                messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt}],\n                temperature=temperature,\n            )\n            return response.content[0].text\n\n        elif self.provider == \"ollama\":\n            import requests\n            full_prompt = f\"{SPARK_VOICE}\\n\\n{prompt}\"\n            response = requests.post(\n                \"http://localhost:11434/api/generate\",\n                json={\n                    \"model\": self.model,\n                    \"prompt\": full_prompt,\n                    \"stream\": False,\n                    \"options\": {\"temperature\": temperature, \"num_predict\": max_tokens},\n                },\n                timeout=90,\n            )\n            return response.json().get(\"response\", \"\").strip()\n\n        raise ValueError(f\"Unknown provider: {self.provider}\")\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774273187491}}
