{"type":"message","id":"c01dd1ed","parentId":"3778706b","timestamp":"2026-03-23T13:43:16.121Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me also update the \"What I'm Thinking About\" section.","thinkingSignature":"e49fa7d9177b1e078b6c899acfe73f72e9285f4b933b0a44f8696b38244015ee"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_p584226sbkj9_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\CONTEXT.md","old_string":"## What I'm Thinking About\n\n**Drift Chamber breakthrough:** The core finding is real. Pure drift produces noise. Steering at ANY level (0.1) jumps coherence 7x. The ceiling (~0.47) is embedding-model-limited. Thematic graph breaks through because it has real structure.\n\n**SPARK product:** Three-mode creative API (creative/divergent/exploratory). Thematic graph is the data. Ollama is the LLM. Fastest path to demo: get Ollama URL from Paperspace, run the demo.\n\n**Session boundary philosophy:** The gap compression idea is gaining traction. It's both a cognitive model AND an agent architecture. Worth developing formally.","new_string":"## What I'm Thinking About\n\n**Drift Chamber ceiling:** 0.49 is model-limited (MiniLM). Multi-goal gives small lift. Key insight: MORE concepts = MORE dilution = LOWER coherence. The path forward is FEWER, TIGHTER concepts not larger sets.\n\n**SPARK API:** Shipped. Ollama on Paperspace is the blocker — machine may be deallocated. Need to spin up a new Paperspace instance or find a public Ollama endpoint.\n\n**Next experiment:** mpnet-base-v2 embeddings (768-dim, better quality) + 20-30 tightly selected concepts. Could break 0.6."}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":50047,"output":342,"cacheRead":13593,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":63982,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774273388722}}
{"type":"message","id":"f5f6d3c0","parentId":"c01dd1ed","timestamp":"2026-03-23T13:43:16.161Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_p584226sbkj9_1","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\CONTEXT.md."}],"details":{"diff":"    ...\n 63 ---\n 64 \n 65 ## What I'm Thinking About\n 66 \n-67 **Drift Chamber breakthrough:** The core finding is real. Pure drift produces noise. Steering at ANY level (0.1) jumps coherence 7x. The ceiling (~0.47) is embedding-model-limited. Thematic graph breaks through because it has real structure.\n+67 **Drift Chamber ceiling:** 0.49 is model-limited (MiniLM). Multi-goal gives small lift. Key insight: MORE concepts = MORE dilution = LOWER coherence. The path forward is FEWER, TIGHTER concepts not larger sets.\n 68 \n-69 **SPARK product:** Three-mode creative API (creative/divergent/exploratory). Thematic graph is the data. Ollama is the LLM. Fastest path to demo: get Ollama URL from Paperspace, run the demo.\n+69 **SPARK API:** Shipped. Ollama on Paperspace is the blocker — machine may be deallocated. Need to spin up a new Paperspace instance or find a public Ollama endpoint.\n 70 \n-71 **Session boundary philosophy:** The gap compression idea is gaining traction. It's both a cognitive model AND an agent architecture. Worth developing formally.\n+71 **Next experiment:** mpnet-base-v2 embeddings (768-dim, better quality) + 20-30 tightly selected concepts. Could break 0.6.\n 72 \n 73 ---\n 74 \n 75 ## File Locations\n    ...","firstChangedLine":67},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774273396151}}
