{"type":"message","id":"3ac02015","parentId":"f7bf8c4d","timestamp":"2026-03-23T13:51:15.030Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"It's running and waiting for the Ollama response. Let me wait for it.","thinkingSignature":"962bdce3a94fad996a7248a6a6b79e439bf5acc6391dbefdd3f136992bdb356c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zoqddxpdaqtr_1","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"poll","sessionId":"tide-bison","timeout":90000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":56062,"output":67,"cacheRead":13593,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69722,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774273872031}}
{"type":"message","id":"5ee4f891","parentId":"3ac02015","timestamp":"2026-03-23T13:51:26.615Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_zoqddxpdaqtr_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[31;1mC:\\Users\\Zwmar\\AppData\\Roaming\\Python\\Python314\\site-packages\\requests\\__init__.py:113: RequestsDependencyWarning: urllib3 (2.6.2) or chardet (6.0.0.post1)/charset_normalizer (3.4.4) doesn't match a supported version![0m\r\n[31;1m  warnings.warn([0m\r\n[SPARK] all graph: 268 concepts, 2732 edges\r\n[SPARK] Steering: 0.3, Mode: creative\r\n[SPARK] Drift complete: 20 strong concepts | entropy: 0.799\r\n[SPARK] Top 10: creativity, imagination, novelty, innovation, invention, originality, divergence, synthesis, transformation, recombination\r\n\r\n============================================================\r\nOUTPUT 1/1\r\n============================================================\r\nIn the dimly lit studio, Kael's fingers danced across the keyboard, her eyes flicking between the screen and a scattered mess of scraps: torn music sheets, discarded sketches, broken vases. The scent of burning incense clung to her skin like a bad habit.\r\n\r\nHer AI assistant, Ada, hummed softly in the corner, a gentle thrum that seemed to amplify Kael's own heartbeat. The words flowed from her like blood from a cut: phrases that tumbled out without warning, images that conjured themselves whole. It was as if the machine had taken on a life of its own, channeling the darkness into something beautiful.\r\n\r\nKael's gaze snapped back to the screen, her eyes locking onto a line she'd written just moments before: \"The city's skin is not its own.\" She felt the thrill of creation coursing through her veins, but alongside it was a twinge of unease. What did it mean to create something that could be replicated? Was this love � or merely a clever mimicry?\r\n\r\nAs Kael's eyes dropped back to the scraps, she noticed one vase had shifted on its own, the shards reflected in a nearby puddle like shattered mirrors. In the glassy surface, she saw her own face staring back, a map of lines and creases that seemed to shift with every breath. The words blurred together on the screen as Kael's thoughts splintered into fragments: What was original? What was true?\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"tide-bison","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[31;1mC:\\Users\\Zwmar\\AppData\\Roaming\\Python\\Python314\\site-packages\\requests\\__init__.py:113: RequestsDependencyWarning: urllib3 (2.6.2) or chardet (6.0.0.post1)/charset_normalizer (3.4.4) doesn't match a supported version![0m\r\n[31;1m  warnings.warn([0m\r\n[SPARK] all graph: 268 concepts, 2732 edges\r\n[SPARK] Steering: 0.3, Mode: creative\r\n[SPARK] Drift complete: 20 strong concepts | entropy: 0.799\r\n[SPARK] Top 10: creativity, imagination, novelty, innovation, invention, originality, divergence, synthesis, transformation, recombination\r\n\r\n============================================================\r\nOUTPUT 1/1\r\n============================================================\r\nIn the dimly lit studio, Kael's fingers danced across the keyboard, her eyes flicking between the screen and a scattered mess of scraps: torn music sheets, discarded sketches, broken vases. The scent of burning incense clung to her skin like a bad habit.\r\n\r\nHer AI assistant, Ada, hummed softly in the corner, a gentle thrum that seemed to amplify Kael's own heartbeat. The words flowed from her like blood from a cut: phrases that tumbled out without warning, images that conjured themselves whole. It was as if the machine had taken on a life of its own, channeling the darkness into something beautiful.\r\n\r\nKael's gaze snapped back to the screen, her eyes locking onto a line she'd written just moments before: \"The city's skin is not its own.\" She felt the thrill of creation coursing through her veins, but alongside it was a twinge of unease. What did it mean to create something that could be replicated? Was this love � or merely a clever mimicry?\r\n\r\nAs Kael's eyes dropped back to the scraps, she noticed one vase had shifted on its own, the shards reflected in a nearby puddle like shattered mirrors. In the glassy surface, she saw her own face staring back, a map of lines and creases that seemed to shift with every breath. The words blurred together on the screen as Kael's thoughts splintered into fragments: What was original? What was true?\r\n","name":"cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects;"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774273886603}}
{"type":"message","id":"373f23cf","parentId":"5ee4f891","timestamp":"2026-03-23T13:51:42.861Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Excellent! The full SPARK pipeline works end-to-end! The drift chamber generated concept activations, and the LLM mapped them to a genuinely decent piece of creative fiction. It's not perfect (Llama 3.2 3B is a small model) but it demonstrates the full concept → text pipeline.\n\nKey results:\n- Graph: 268 concepts, 2732 edges\n- Strong concepts: 20 (after drift)\n- Entropy: 0.799\n- Top 10: creativity, imagination, novelty, innovation, invention, originality, divergence, synthesis, transformation, recombination\n\nThe prose is genuinely not bad for a 3B model — it's got sensory detail, emotional complexity, and thematic depth about \"love in the age of AI.\"\n \nNow I should update the CONTEXT.md with the Ollama findings and share this with Zach.","thinkingSignature":"da18d9f5d1d2e294dcbdf1368d6d36e628485ccfb70a18e592e67df34d6ea553"},{"type":"text","text":"Full pipeline works end-to-end. Here's what just happened:\n\n**Drift output:** 20 strong concepts — `creativity, imagination, novelty, innovation, invention, originality, divergence, synthesis, transformation, recombination`\n\n**Generated text:**\n> *In the dimly lit studio, Kael's fingers danced across the keyboard... The words flowed from her like blood from a cut... She felt the thrill of creation coursing through her veins, but alongside it was a twinge of unease. What did it mean to create something that could be replicated? Was this love — or merely a clever mimicry?*\n\nThat's Llama 3.2 3B on local Ollama, zero cloud GPU needed for testing. The 3B model shows the limits — it's good but not great. The Qwen 7B on Paperspace would be meaningfully better.\n\n**Summary of what's shipping today:**\n- ✅ Sandbox pulse bug fixed\n- ✅ Drift Chamber ceiling: 0.49 (MiniLM-limited, not model-limited)\n- ✅ SPARK API server ready (`uvicorn spark.api.main:app --port 8765`)\n- ✅ End-to-end demo works with local Ollama (`llama3.2:3b`)\n\n**Remaining gap:** Paperspace Gradient API is **deprecated** as of July 2024 — can't programmatically spin up the Qwen notebook anymore. Need a new GPU cloud plan. Options: Modal (has free tier + A100s), Lambda Labs, or rerun on a new Paperspace account."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":56621,"output":489,"cacheRead":13593,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":70703,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774273886617}}
