{"type":"message","id":"35126512","parentId":"3e7d57b4","timestamp":"2026-03-23T13:53:36.043Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The account has no machines. So the machine was deallocated/deleted. This confirms the old Paperspace Gradient notebook approach won't work - the machine is gone.\n\nThe API is live and working correctly. There are simply no machines in the account. So to get Ollama on a GPU, we need to either:\n1. Create a new machine via the Paperspace Core API (requires knowing the right machine type/template IDs)\n2. Use a different GPU provider\n\nLooking at the OpenAPI spec, there's a `/machines` POST endpoint for creating machines. It requires `machineType` and `os` template IDs. We'd need to know what GPU machine types are available.\n\n\nI should check what OS templates and machine types are available to see what GPU options we can provision.","thinkingSignature":"6b3ad8bbb73689c7efcdbfa9aed7ce161b112b8a3115cc68ce12a89a7917fd7f"},{"type":"text","text":"Good news — the Paperspace API works. Bad news — zero machines in the account. The old notebook is gone. Let me see what GPU machine types are available so we can spin up a new one.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_r3v0hmsmu6mq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$resp = Invoke-RestMethod \"https://api.paperspace.com/v1/osTemplates\" -Headers @{\"Authorization\"=\"Bearer 131e4cbc99405a0e3af9710cc1607c\"}; $resp.items | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 3"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":69827,"output":284,"cacheRead":13593,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":83704,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774274007209}}
