{"type":"message","id":"f78bccfa","parentId":"048f020b","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:06:56.605Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, if `zstd` needs to be installed first, and the `curl -fsSL... | sh` is the next RUN command, they won't be in the same layer. I need `zstd` to be installed before the curl command. Since each `run_commands` is a separate layer, I should put them in the same command or use two separate run_commands calls where zstd comes first. Actually, looking at the Modal API, `run_commands` runs at build time as a RUN command. Multiple calls to `run_commands` will be separate RUN layers.\n\nActually, the issue is that `curl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh` runs the Ollama installer script. The installer checks for zstd and exits if it's not found. \n\nSince they're separate layers, the installer won't find zstd even if I install it first. I need to combine both into a single `run_commands` call so zstd is available when the installer runs.","thinkingSignature":"ab8c985f2fd9a84077cf110efbe2e3905cefa678719bcda84206248ac3f5a771"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hyli7bk4t0a4_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\deploy\\modal_ollama.py","old_string":"    .run_commands(\n        \"apt-get update && apt-get install -y curl zstd\",\n        \"curl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh\",\n    )","new_string":"    .run_commands(\n        \"apt-get update && apt-get install -y curl zstd && curl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh\",\n    )"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":30656,"output":341,"cacheRead":13593,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44590,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774274807316}}
