{"type":"message","id":"03c26344","parentId":"2699dbb0","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:09:00.001Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, actually, in FastAPI, the `path` parameter would set the route path. But in Modal's fastapi_endpoint, the first positional argument is `label`, and there's no `path` parameter. Let me check the Modal API docs... Actually, looking at the Modal SDK, `fastapi_endpoint` takes `label` as the main identifier, and the path is auto-generated from the function name. But if two functions have the same label, they'll get merged.\n\nA cleaner fix: just redeploy with different labels. The health and generate endpoints will get different auto-generated paths based on their function names.","thinkingSignature":"c2f2feb9c05d5f5b6942b11c1cd497b16fc47194441076803276be6fdb28fb8d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_sd1182q0nfqq_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\deploy\\modal_ollama.py","old_string":"    @modal.fastapi_endpoint(label=\"spark-ollama-qwen\", method=\"GET\")\n    def health(self):","new_string":"    @modal.fastapi_endpoint(label=\"spark-ollama-qwen-health\", path=\"/health\")\n    def health(self):"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":80778,"output":240,"cacheRead":13593,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":94611,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774274932726}}
